name: Power of Three - Recycled Bike tube earrings
description:
The power of three is strong in these earrings. Made using recycled bicycle inner tubes. Each earring has three triangle shaped pieces overlapping each other held to the hook by black chain.

Check out the listing for the matching "Power of Three" necklace (shown in the last picture)
https://www.etsy.com/listing/115676489/power-of-three-recycled-bike-tube

The inner tube material has a unique texture that looks almost like leather but is very light and durable. Most people who see these earrings can't believe they are made out of rubber inner tubes until they actually touch them. All the tubes I use are beyond repair and have been saved from going in to the landfill.

Jewelry you can actually feel good about wearing and giving as gifts.

All earrings are hand cut, painted and assembled by me in Oakland, California. 

***You will NOT receive the exact pair the model is wearing. A fresh new pair is made for each sale so the earrings you receive will never have been worn before.

name: Native solitary - Recycled Bike Tube Earrings
description:
Feather shaped earrings made using recycled bicycle inner tubes. Each earring has one large solid feather with thin wisps that have been hand cut into the sides. The earring hook is silver plated and kidney bean shaped which closes completely in to a loop to protect your earrings from falling out of your ears. These are great for riding your bike, no need to worry about your earrings flying off while racing down that hill.
The sliver plating is great for people who have sensitive ears.

The inner tube material has a unique texture that looks almost like leather but is very light and durable.
